forrie@decvax.dec.com (Forrest Aldrich) writes:

>I was just viewing the program "Beyond 2000" on the Discovery Channel...
>they spoke of a new means by which to store and retrieve data via laser-printed
>"strips" on paper.  Just a few strips of these could represent up to 12 pages of
>type-written data and more... plus, it can be used to store encrypted data on
>credit cards...

It's a product that AT&T announced a few months ago.  The message can be 
reconstitued after scanning the "random apparing" page into a computer 
that undoes the encryption.  

An alternative is to send the encrypted message directly
to a laptop with the decryption software.

